Citation.sTitle: Molecular interactions in (2,4,6-trimethyl-1,3,5-trioxane + n-alkyl acetates) at T=(298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of the binary mixtures of 2,4,6-trimethyl-1,3,5-trioxane with methyl acetate, ethyl acetate, and 1-butyl acetate were measured over the entire mole fractions at (298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K. Using the experimental values of densities q and viscosities g, excess molar volumes VE, viscosity deviations dg were calculated. The values of excess molar volumes VE and viscosity deviations dg were fitted to the Redlich-Kister polynomial.
